  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "I have an app that's served as `xml`. Recent react version [supports xml](https://github.com/facebook/react/issues/2278). However, it looks like controlled components are broken. I created a demo \nhttps://github.com/neojski/random/tree/gh-pages/react-input-xml-error. These are two almost identical pages with one named `xhtml` and the other one `html`. The only difference is:\n\n``` diff\n1c1\n< <html>\n\n---\n> <html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n```\n\nOn the `xhtml` one input's value may be changed. It's a controlled input that never changes the `state` property so its value shouldn't be mutable. It works as expected on the `html` page.\n",
